# Frontend React conventions

## Stack

- React 19 functional components only (no class components).
- Ant Design 6 for UI primitives (`Splitter`, `Drawer`, `Table`, `Select`, etc.).
- uPlot in `components/plot/PlotPanel.tsx` for charts — do not swap in Recharts/ECharts without user request.
- Zustand for shared state in `stores/`; local `useState` only for component-private UI (e.g. open/closed).

## Structure

- Entry: `App.tsx` → `components/layout/AppShell.tsx`.
- Add feature UI under `components/<feature>/`, not in `AppShell` when avoidable.
- Shared types live in `api/types.ts`; do not duplicate interfaces in components.

## Patterns

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — API client in a component
function Tree() {
  const client = new SmcServerClient(...);
}

// ✅ GOOD — callbacks from useWatchIo via AppShell
<VariableTree onLoadVariables={(branch) => client.current?.fetchVarLeaves(branch)} />
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — fetch connection config from env in random components
const url = import.meta.env.VITE_HTTP_URL;

// ✅ GOOD — read from connectionStore
const { config } = useConnectionStore();
```

## Styling

- Use existing classes in `App.css` / `index.css`.
- Match Iris-style layout: header (menu + connection bar), split panes, footer status line.
- Footer status classes: `footer-status--connected`, `--error`, `--connecting`, `--disconnected`.

## Code language

- All identifiers, comments, and user-visible strings in **English** (see `language-conventions.mdc`).

